News of the Day From Across the Nation, March 24Image 1 of / 1 Caption Close News of the Day From Across the Nation, March 24 1 / 1 Back to Gallery1 Cohen rebuffed: A former personal lawyer for President Trump was denied early release from a three-year prison sentence Tuesday after he pleaded guilty to numerous charges, including campaign finance fraud and lying to Congress.
2 Deputies cleared: Three South Carolina sheriff’s deputies won’t face any criminal charges after they fatally shot a man during a domestic dispute, authorities said.
Deputies responded to a domestic disturbance call on Dec. 10 at Bateman’s home just outside of Andrews, authorities said.
Court documents said counterfeiters presented themselves as Walmart executives and persuaded inexperienced cashiers to cash fake checks with routing numbers tied to banks, including of Bank of America and PNC Bank.
The counterfeiters would use the checks to purchase prepaid Walmart debit cards, then use the cards to buy merchandise they would later return for cash, documents said.